#### Title: Developing Efficient Planning Algorithms for Complex Logical Features and Compositions of Binary Relations

#### Abstract
This research aims to develop planning algorithms that efficiently handle complex logical features and compositions of binary relations while maintaining computational efficiency. By introducing a parameterized version of Relational Graph Neural Networks (R-GNNs), we aim to balance the expressive power required for complex logical features with the computational efficiency needed for practical applications.

