 of policy sketches in automated planning and decision-making.\n   - Discuss the potential benefits of integrating policy sketches with R-GNNs.\n\n4. **State Symmetry Detection:**\n   - Review existing methods for state symmetry detection in planning domains.\n   - Discuss the importance of state symmetry detection in improving learning efficiency and reducing the search space.\n\nBy completing these steps, the research proposal will be more comprehensive and ready for further development or submission.\n\n### Final Research Proposal\n\n**Title:** Developing a Scalable and Expressive Model for Learning General Policies in Automated Planning Using Parameterized R-GNNs and Policy Sketches\n\n**Abstract:**\nThis research aims to develop a scalable and expressive model for learning general policies in automated planning that can handle complex logical features. The proposed approach involves developing a parameterized version of R-GNNs that can balance expressive power with computational effort. The method will involve transforming the input set of atoms to capture complex logical features and using a parameter \\( t \\) to control the level of approximation. The dataset will consist of planning problems with complex logical features, and the metrics will include policy performance and computational efficiency. The expected outcomes include a scalable and expressive model for learning general policies in automated planning.\n\n**Introduction:**\nMachine learning, particularly in the context of automated planning and decision-making, is limited by its ability to learn general policies that can handle complex logical features. Current approaches, whether combinatorial or deep learning-based, struggle with capturing the nuances of complex logical structures, leading to suboptimal policies and scalability issues.\n\n**Methodology:**\n1. **Input Transformation:**\n   - Logical Feature Extraction\n   - Graph Construction\n2. **Parameter \\( t \\) Control:**\n   - Approximation Levels\n   - Adaptive Learning\n3. **Model Training:**\n   - Parameterized R-GNNs\n   - Policy Sketch Integration\n4. **Model Evaluation:**\n   - Performance Metrics\n   - Iterative Improvement\n\n**Datasets:**\n- Benchmark Planning Domains\n- Synthetic Datasets\n\n**Preprocessing Steps:**\n- Logical Feature Extraction\n- Graph Construction\n- Normalization\n\n**Evaluation Metrics:**\n- Policy Performance\n- Computational Efficiency\n- Scalability\n\n**Expected Outcomes:**\n- Scalable and Expressive Model\n- Balanced Expressiveness and Efficiency\n- Iterative Improvement\n\n**Literature Review:**\n- Existing Approaches\n- Parameterized R-GNNs\n- Policy Sketches\n- State Symmetry Detection\n\nThis comprehensive research proposal is now ready for further development or submission."}

