sive power with computational effort. The method will involve transforming the input set of atoms to capture complex logical features and using a parameter \\( t \\) to control the level of approximation. The dataset will consist of planning problems with complex logical features, and the metrics will include policy performance and computational efficiency. The expected outcomes include a scalable and expressive model for learning general policies in automated planning.\n\n### Next Task\n\nThe next task is to finalize the research proposal by:\n\n1. **Refining the Methodology:** Provide more detailed steps and techniques for transforming the input set of atoms and controlling the parameter \\( t \\).\n2. **Dataset Selection:** Specify the datasets that will be used for training and testing the model, including any preprocessing steps.\n3. **Evaluation Metrics:** Define the specific metrics that will be used to evaluate the performance of the model, such as accuracy, efficiency, and scalability.\n4. **Expected Outcomes:** Clearly outline the expected outcomes and how they will demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach.\n5. **Literature Review:** Ensure that the proposal includes a thorough literature review that contextualizes the research within the existing body of work.\n\nBy completing these steps, the research proposal will be more comprehensive and ready for further development or submission.", 'agent2': "Given the detailed analysis and the proposed research idea, the next logical step is to refine the research proposal and ensure that it is clear, concise, and well-structured. This includes further elaborating on the methodology, expected results, and any additional details that might be necessary to make the proposal compelling and actionable. Here’s a suggested next task:\n\n### Refine the Research Proposal\n\n**Objective:** To refine the research proposal based on the '5q' format, ensuring clarity, coherence, and completeness.\n\n**Steps:**\n\n